### Health
GET http://localhost:3001/health

### Signup student
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student12@example.com",
  "password": "pass1234"
}

### Login student (get access + refresh)
# @name loginStudent
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student12@example.com",
  "password": "pass1234"
}

### Unauthorized access should be 401
GET http://localhost:3001/api/signup

### Student create participant
# @name createP
POST http://localhost:3001/api/signup
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStudent.response.body.token}}

{
  "name": "小明 Week12",
  "email": "student12@example.com",
  "phone": "0912345678"
}

### Student list (only own)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/signup
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStudent.response.body.token}}

### Refresh access token using refreshToken (bonus)
# @name refreshStudent
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{loginStudent.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### Forgot password (bonus) - demo returns resetToken
# @name forgot
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/forgot
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student12@example.com"
}

### Reset password (bonus)
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resetToken": "{{forgot.response.body.resetToken}}",
  "newPassword": "newpass123"
}

### Login with new password (bonus validation)
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student12@example.com",
  "password": "newpass123"
}

### Login admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin1234"
}

### Admin list all
GET http://localhost:3001/api/signup
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.token}}

### Admin audit logs (bonus)
GET http://localhost:3001/admin/audit-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.token}}
